just_use claude_landing.go

# label: EARLY
# role: Gopher view — /gopher/claude; a two-card sub-landing
#       that points out to the claude-collab repo

Minimal sub-landing. Reached from the Claude card on the
home page and from the top-bar Claude area. Contains no
dynamic content — two cards with links to the local
claude-collab essay server (port 9100) and to the
claude-collab GitHub repo.

Created 2026-04-21 after the ANCHOR_COMMENTS rip, which
removed the older claude_landing.go that linked to the
now-deleted Essays/Issues. The current file is a simple
pointer-out now that the essay format lives in a separate
repo.

## Pointers

- Consumer: routed in `views/registry.go` at `/gopher/claude`
  and `/gopher/claude/`.
- Related memory: `reference_port_convention.md` (9000 vs
  9100).
